Comment: 0,0:13:59.34,0:14:04.32,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,{\an7\fs32\move(10,20,10,20,40,-2)}This is a dumb riddle about rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.18,0:00:10.70,BakumanDialogue,iwase,0,0,0,,I'm second?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.74,0:00:13.04,BakumanDialogue,boys,0,0,0,,Amazing, Takagi! You're #1!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.28,0:00:15.02,BakumanDialogue,boys,0,0,0,,And you only ever read manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.26,0:00:17.06,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,Just studying all the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.50,0:00:19.28,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,Going to a good high school and a good college...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.08,0:00:21.28,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,That kind of thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.34,0:00:23.24,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,isn't my dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.98,0:00:25.68,BakumanDialogueTop,boys,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.68,0:00:26.42,BakumanDialogueTop,boys,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.42,0:00:27.98,BakumanDialogueTop,boys,0,0,0,,Get it over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.86,0:00:31.38,BakumanDialogueTop,boys,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.06,0:00:32.34,BakumanDialogue,iwase,0,0,0,,I still can't let my guard down.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.18,0:00:56.10,BakumanDialogue,iwase,0,0,0,,Takagi-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.38,0:01:00.88,BakumanDialogue,iwase,0,0,0,,I'm Iwase Aiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.36,0:01:05.14,BakumanDialogue,iwase,0,0,0,,The 2nd highest grades in our class,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.56,0:01:06.70,BakumanDialogue,iwase,0,0,0,,that was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.84,0:01:08.24,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,Oh... really?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.78,0:01:15.48,BakumanDialogue,iwase,0,0,0,,I think we should encourage\Neach other and do our best.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.18,0:01:18.92,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.60,0:01:21.50,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,Let's do our best.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.06,0:01:30.24,BakumanDialogue,iwase,0,0,0,,This is Akina.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.16,0:01:31.92,BakumanDialogue,iwase,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.88,0:01:34.80,BakumanDialogue,iwase,0,0,0,,The collaboration with {\i1}Crow{\i0} took 4th place.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.64,0:01:36.74,BakumanDialogue,iwase,0,0,0,,What about {\i1}PCP?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.72,0:01:38.36,BakumanDialogue,iwase,0,0,0,,5th?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.10,0:01:40.42,BakumanDialogue,iwase,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.12,0:01:42.80,BakumanDialogue,iwase,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.22,0:01:45.96,BakumanDialogue,iwase,0,0,0,,I said I wouldn't lose to {\i1}PCP.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.10,0:02:20.32,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,Hey, if I could be with you right now
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.16,0:02:29.67,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,Then I could keep my voice from fading
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.33,0:02:36.38,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,The goals I've set for myself seem too high to reach,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.38,0:02:40.84,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,and I feel like I've lost my way
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.39,0:02:50.44,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,I'm relying on a broken compass and hiding in someone's shadow
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.52,0:03:01.78,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,If we keep letting go of what we have to find something else,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.78,0:03:11.87,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1100)}then I'm convinced we can never grow up
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.50,0:03:17.71,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1100)}Never
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.42,0:03:22.34,BakumanTitle,title,0,0,0,,{\c&HFFFFFF&}Last and Cipher
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.40,0:03:25.02,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,5th in the survey.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.24,0:03:27.38,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Even with the cover and color pages...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.38,0:03:29.46,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,but isn't this a little unfair?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.46,0:03:31.20,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,The collaboration with {\i1}Crow...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.70,0:03:32.86,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,It isn't unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.06,0:03:35.40,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to be popular,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.40,0:03:38.30,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,you have to do everything that\Nyou can to make it interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.44,0:03:39.64,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,We're professionals, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.20,0:03:44.40,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,When Eiji said he wouldn't lose\Nto {\i1}PCP, {\i0}we should have listened.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.60,0:03:46.50,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought Iwase was underestimating him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.00,0:03:47.98,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Now we know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.16,0:03:49.28,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Akina Aiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.44,0:03:51.06,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like you said Shujin,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.06,0:03:52.54,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,she's become a good rival.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.68,0:03:53.82,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.46,0:03:58.18,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Gah! The cover and color\Npages were our big chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.18,0:03:59.48,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,We're screwed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.60,0:04:03.06,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,We have until chapter 25,\Nthat leaves 6 more chapters.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.32,0:04:05.30,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how long we have to figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.20,0:04:07.98,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Or else we'll be cancelled.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.54,0:04:12.76,BakumanDialogue,miura,0,0,0,,Man, I knew that collaboration was a good idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.76,0:04:15.42,BakumanDialogue,miura,0,0,0,,Takahama-kun's {\i1}Ally of Justice{\i0} is in 6th.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.42,0:04:18.68,BakumanDialogue,miura,0,0,0,,I'm the editor for 4th and 6th place! I'm headed for the top!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.68,0:04:19.90,BakumanDialogueTop,yuujiro,0,0,0,,Not happening!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.90,0:04:21.34,BakumanDialogueTop,yuujiro,0,0,0,,You think I'll just let it happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.58,0:04:23.28,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,The gap between us and +Natural is widening...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.98,0:04:24.78,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,That's not all...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.78,0:04:27.84,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ally of Justice{\i0} is in 6th place, just 10 votes behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.98,0:04:30.50,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,And {\i1}Road Racer Giri{\i0} is right behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.72,0:04:32.58,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,This is a fight from below...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.04,0:04:36.70,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,{\i1}Crow{\i0} and {\i1}+Natural{\i0} have the most 1st place votes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.84,0:04:39.14,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,But {\i1}PCP{\i0} has a lot of 3rd place votes...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.92,0:04:42.78,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,This is a survey where people\Nrank series in order of interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.14,0:04:45.26,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,But 4th place votes don't count at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.82,0:04:48.24,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,I need to think of a way to raise our votes!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.24,0:04:51.92,BakumanDialogueTop,yuujiro,0,0,0,,You may think that, but {\i1}Crow{\i0} won't lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.62,0:04:52.10,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,No, wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.96,0:04:54.58,BakumanDialogueTop,miura,0,0,0,,It was just a joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.58,0:04:55.68,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,That's not it at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.68,0:04:56.30,BakumanDialogue,miura,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.96,0:04:57.90,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,It's the opposite...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.78,0:05:00.14,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.14,0:05:01.28,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,The opposite?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.52,0:05:04.36,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,When it comes to 3rd place votes, {\i1}PCP{\i0} is #1.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.46,0:05:05.38,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Basically,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.48,0:05:08.40,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,A lot of people think that {\i1}PCP{\i0}\Nis the third most interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.40,0:05:12.40,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,The votes for 1st place are really divided.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.54,0:05:14.84,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that kind of bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.84,0:05:15.42,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.42,0:05:17.04,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Think about it the other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.48,0:05:20.28,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,You have to be careful with a manga\Nthat gets a lot of 3rd place votes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.28,0:05:25.38,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,If they turn into 4th place votes,\Nthey don't count for anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.36,0:05:28.76,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,What if we counted 4th place votes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.76,0:05:30.96,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,What would our ranking look like then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.10,0:05:32.12,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.32,0:05:34.10,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,If we can bump up all of\Nthe possible 4th place votes,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.10,0:05:39.66,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,, {\i1}PCP{\i0} would have a major boost\Nwhen it came to the final ranking.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.98,0:05:42.42,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,So we just need to find a way to turn\N4th place votes into 3rd place votes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.62,0:05:43.52,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.56,0:05:47.90,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Turning 4th place votes into 3rd...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.56,0:05:50.72,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,If we can just find a way to give a little impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.86,0:05:52.00,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Impact...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.00,0:05:52.74,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.10,0:05:55.26,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Like when {\i1}Crow{\i0} had no text.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.56,0:05:58.12,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,But we can't do that with {\i1}PCP.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.12,0:06:00.60,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,That's something only Niizuma-kun can pull off.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.78,0:06:03.62,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,For Takagi-kun, it's better to have more lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.62,0:06:04.22,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.60,0:06:07.78,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,But don't series with too\Nmany lines perform poorly?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.78,0:06:09.12,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,That isn't necessarily true.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.40,0:06:12.48,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,For example, {\i1}Ally of Justice{\i0} took 6th place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.72,0:06:15.46,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,It almost caught up with {\i1}PCP.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.84,0:06:18.06,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,And it had a lot of lines...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.26,0:06:19.92,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the way a trial is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.20,0:06:22.10,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was pretty interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.10,0:06:24.64,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,And the readers read every bit of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.88,0:06:27.52,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Especially the ones who fill out the survey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.14,0:06:28.98,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.16,0:06:30.42,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ally of Justice...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.42,0:06:32.28,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,{\bord2}Do you know what rankings it has had?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.48,0:06:33.68,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.30,0:06:35.48,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Chapter 1 was in 3rd.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.48,0:06:36.92,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Chapters 2 and 3 were in 7th.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.92,0:06:38.24,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Chapter 4 was 9th.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.34,0:06:40.42,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,And this chapter ended the case in 6th place.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.56,0:06:42.00,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,From 9th to 6th...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.72,0:06:45.40,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,With {\i1}Trap{\i0}, the same thing happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.40,0:06:47.24,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.24,0:06:48.32,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.86,0:06:50.88,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,We have 6 chapters left until chapter 25.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.08,0:06:54.10,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think about a 5-chapter series?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.10,0:06:54.80,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.00,0:06:58.82,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,, If the series has a good ending,\Nthe impact will raise our ranking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.96,0:07:02.08,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ally of Justice{\i0} and {\i1}Trap{\i0} have proved that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.08,0:07:03.20,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,That's too risky...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.36,0:07:05.94,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,If you do 1-chapter stories, you have 5 chances.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.02,0:07:08.86,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,But with a 5-chapter arc, you have\Njust one chance and then it's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.98,0:07:13.06,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,And the rating will drop until you reach a good climax.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.44,0:07:15.28,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,With that kind of disadvantage...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.28,0:07:17.08,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,it would be too difficult\Nto catch up at the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.12,0:07:17.80,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.18,0:07:19.34,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if we do a series,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.34,0:07:21.72,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,and keep things at the same level...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.72,0:07:24.94,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,we can make it build to a really big climax.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.94,0:07:25.78,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,That may be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.78,0:07:28.86,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,But with an arc, the freshness of the perfect crimes is lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.10,0:07:32.86,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,And anyone who reads a chapter out\Nof context won't understand the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.86,0:07:36.36,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Readers will read everything thoroughly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.52,0:07:38.90,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you just say that, Hattori-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.62,0:07:43.28,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,, In one-chapter stories, nothing big\Ncan happen to Makoto and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.12,0:07:45.98,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,For more than 16 chapters...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.14,0:07:47.74,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,we've been following the same pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.74,0:07:50.84,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,With a 5 chapter arc we could make big things happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.46,0:07:52.58,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.86,0:07:53.94,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Saiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.86,0:07:57.02,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Crow and +Natural...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.26,0:07:59.08,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,keep pulling ahead of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.74,0:08:02.74,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think we can win on our current path.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.54,0:08:06.66,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Please let us do a series!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.66,0:08:07.90,BakumanDialogue,mashiro,0,0,0,,Please let us!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.90,0:08:08.96,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,Hattori-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.92,0:08:11.90,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,Have you thought of a plot for the series?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.90,0:08:14.28,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,, No, I'll think about it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.28,0:08:16.70,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,Mashiro has worked hard to improve the art,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.94,0:08:19.38,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,so now it's time for me to work on the story!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.64,0:08:22.76,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,It may seem arrogant, but this is\Nabout our continued serialization.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.76,0:08:25.20,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,If we get cancelled this time, it will be our third.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.20,0:08:26.96,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,Our lives as authors are riding on this!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.42,0:08:30.18,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,Please let us do it the way we believe we should!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.70,0:08:35.88,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,A while ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.48,0:08:40.46,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,I said a manga author had to surpass their editor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.96,0:08:43.08,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,Honestly,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.26,0:08:45.96,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,I think this series is too big of a risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.42,0:08:51.08,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,But you guys are always exceeding my expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.72,0:08:56.02,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,Mashiro-kun, you can create a manuscript\Nfrom a storyboard that is only text.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.70,0:08:59.12,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,And you found and fixed the\Nproblems with your own art.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.68,0:09:00.72,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,And now,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.80,0:09:03.66,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,Takagi-kun's desire to do a story arc.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.24,0:09:07.06,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,You reached those conclusions before I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.24,0:09:09.24,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,I'm so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.00,0:09:11.34,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,In these 6 years...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.34,0:09:13.06,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,you have both grown.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.78,0:09:14.72,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,Amazingly!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.82,0:09:16.90,BakumanDialogue,mashiro,0,0,0,,Hattori-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.44,0:09:18.34,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,Takagi-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.06,0:09:19.94,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,Mashiro-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.70,0:09:23.60,BakumanDialogue,hattori,0,0,0,,Follow what you believe with all your heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.60,0:09:24.50,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.54,0:09:28.34,BakumanDialogue,kaya,0,0,0,,Then, while I'm waiting...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.34,0:09:30.34,BakumanDialogue,kaya,0,0,0,,we could have a girls date!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.04,0:09:32.16,BakumanDialogue,azuki,0,0,0,,"Date,"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.46,0:09:34.82,BakumanDialogue,azuki,0,0,0,,it would be bad if Takagi-kun heard that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.82,0:09:36.28,BakumanDialogue,kaya,0,0,0,,It's fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.28,0:09:39.72,BakumanDialogue,kaya,0,0,0,,Today he had a meeting with\Nthe editor and he isn't home yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.96,0:09:42.72,BakumanDialogue,kaya,0,0,0,,He won't need dinner when he gets home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.32,0:09:45.20,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,I'm home!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.00,0:09:46.94,BakumanDialogue,kaya,0,0,0,,Oh, he's home!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.12,0:09:49.32,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,I'm working on the story,\Nso I'll sleep at the studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.32,0:09:50.46,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.46,0:09:52.10,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,Well, I love you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.88,0:09:53.38,BakumanDialogue,kaya,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.60,0:09:55.10,BakumanDialogue,takagi,0,0,0,,Alright, let's do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.24,0:09:58.06,BakumanDialogue,kaya,0,0,0,,He sounds really fired up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.06,0:09:59.26,BakumanDialogue,kaya,0,0,0,,It's kind of weird...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.30,0:10:02.36,BakumanDialogue,kaya,0,0,0,,Oh, and it's raining tomorrow, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.76,0:10:05.34,BakumanDialogue,azuki,0,0,0,, Well, I guess he'll get wet!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.24,0:10:10.72,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright, so tell me about the plot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.72,0:10:11.92,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.70,0:10:14.44,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you alright, Shujin?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.04,0:10:18.90,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,PCP's rival will be one of their classmates.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.24,0:10:20.68,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.86,0:10:23.40,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Akechi-kun is smart and\Nhas good deductive skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.94,0:10:28.98,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,He realizes that something is going on in class 3-5, and he says he's going to expose them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.50,0:10:32.32,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,The members of PCP have a meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.32,0:10:34.42,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,The next day, there is a notice posted in the classroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.98,0:10:36.50,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Today during lunch,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.50,0:10:38.74,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,something good will happen for class 5-3.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.24,0:10:42.74,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, class 5-3 gets pudding for dessert.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.92,0:10:46.38,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't that expose PCP?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.38,0:10:47.10,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.28,0:10:49.16,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,This is PCP's trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.16,0:10:50.00,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Trap?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.88,0:10:52.88,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Who will look the most suspicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.26,0:10:55.22,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he told everyone about it, Akechi will.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.52,0:10:57.24,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.24,0:10:58.12,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,That makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.82,0:11:00.76,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Akechi still wants to catch the real culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.76,0:11:04.54,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,So he has classmates watch him 24/7.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.94,0:11:08.84,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,But PCP notices, and stops their operations.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.00,0:11:11.28,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,So everyone assumes it was Akechi after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.44,0:11:13.48,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as PCP planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.64,0:11:16.56,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,And then Akechi admits that he was the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.56,0:11:19.36,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,And tells everyone to stop searching.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.36,0:11:21.58,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,What? He claims responsibility?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.98,0:11:24.64,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,But that's part of his plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.92,0:11:29.60,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,PCP lets their guard down\Nand starts operating again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.60,0:11:33.70,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Akechi still has friends that he can trust watching him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.18,0:11:36.30,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,That would prove that he isn't the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.50,0:11:37.52,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Not bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.68,0:11:42.22,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Akechi figures out that there is more than one culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.40,0:11:44.30,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,PCP starts to worry again,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.92,0:11:46.68,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,and the chapter ends with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.24,0:11:49.44,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,The first chapter introduces Akechi's character.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.66,0:11:52.30,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Chapters 2 and 3 focus on PCP's crimes,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.30,0:11:55.08,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,and on the announcements and investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.62,0:11:57.10,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,That sounds pretty cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.30,0:11:59.14,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.14,0:11:59.98,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.16,0:12:02.86,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't think of anything for chapters 4 and 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.90,0:12:03.64,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.74,0:12:07.72,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Chapter 4 should have PCP send a challenge to Akechi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.16,0:12:12.26,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,It says that if he can stop their crime,\Nthey will reveal themselves to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.26,0:12:15.58,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, chapter 5 is where the\Nmost important stuff happens...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.94,0:12:19.54,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,but I still can't think of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.78,0:12:20.78,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.26,0:12:24.64,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the challenge will determine\Nhow interesting the whole series is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.46,0:12:27.10,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.58,0:12:31.62,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a good outline, but the\Nlast chapters are the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.74,0:12:33.74,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,While you're writing the first three,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.74,0:12:35.92,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,you could think about 4 and 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.98,0:12:37.34,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,That won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.48,0:12:40.96,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Beating {\i1}+Natural{\i0} and {\i1}Crow{\i0} is the purpose of the series.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.42,0:12:43.32,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,If you don't know the ending,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.32,0:12:46.32,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,you'll be better off making single-chapter stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.28,0:12:49.24,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.40,0:12:50.70,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,A cool ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.06,0:12:53.42,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll give it some thought too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.76,0:12:56.30,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,But the dialog and plot are your job, Takagi-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.66,0:12:57.90,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,So good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.20,0:13:00.28,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.20,0:13:03.32,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,If I can't think of a story,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.24,0:13:05.96,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll never beat Iwase.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.16,0:13:15.48,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Vice Principal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.38,0:13:18.20,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the Principal now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.40,0:13:21.72,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're writing manga now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.72,0:13:24.28,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,It's pretty popular with the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.58,0:13:41.38,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,So you went to the elementary school?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.60,0:13:43.62,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it really brought me back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.86,0:13:45.82,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,So did you get any ideas?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.82,0:13:48.22,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.80,0:13:51.36,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I've got a message.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.10,0:13:52.90,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Azuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.90,0:13:53.64,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.74,0:13:54.58,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.78,0:13:56.72,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing, the message doesn't mean much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.84,0:13:57.70,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.26,0:13:59.34,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.34,0:14:04.32,BakumanSMS,,0,0,150,,{\fad(0,1000)\an8\frz0.7185\move(558.666,116.667,557.333,59.334,40,4961)}Some people need the rain
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.34,0:14:04.32,BakumanSMS,,0,0,150,,{\fad(0,1000)\an8\frz0.7185\move(562.667,175.333,561.334,118,40,4961)}But for some other people,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.34,0:14:04.32,BakumanSMS,,0,0,150,,{\fad(0,1000)\an8\frz0.7185\move(605.333,288.667,606.666,232.667,40,4961)}Can be a really bad thing, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.34,0:14:04.32,BakumanSMS,,0,0,150,,{\fad(0,1000)\an8\frz0.7185\move(504.001,232.667,502.668,175.334,40,4961)}Too  much  rain  . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.70,0:14:02.26,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Azuki sends some strange messages from time to time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.62,0:14:06.62,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,If I ask what they mean, she just says "what?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.62,0:14:08.12,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,So I just say "that's true".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.56,0:14:13.20,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,On your phone, how many letters does it show per line?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.20,0:14:15.32,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? 12 letters I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.52,0:14:16.80,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,That's normal, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.98,0:14:17.58,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.80,0:14:19.34,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Mine is 12 too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.22,0:14:21.06,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.26,0:14:22.08,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.78,0:14:28.58,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,PCP doesn't want their phone number\Ngetting out, so they have a group phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.58,0:14:29.86,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not too unbelievable, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.86,0:14:30.82,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.82,0:14:33.14,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,It's manga, so that should be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.14,0:14:34.22,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.22,0:14:37.82,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,From that phone they send Akechi a message.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.82,0:14:38.76,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.76,0:14:40.98,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,"Between 8 and 8:30,"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.98,0:14:43.82,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'm going to set off fireworks on the school grounds."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.82,0:14:47.60,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,"If you can stop me, I'll reveal my identity."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.80,0:14:48.98,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Fireworks...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.98,0:14:50.78,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a good item for summer!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.78,0:14:51.60,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.80,0:14:54.68,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,He has until that time on that day\Nto identify the fireworks culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.68,0:14:56.74,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,He'll have to stake out the campus.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.22,0:15:01.00,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,We can draw it like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.14,0:15:01.76,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.76,0:15:05.66,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,When the time comes, Akechi\Ndoesn't know who the culprit is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.66,0:15:06.60,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,What would you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.64,0:15:08.46,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.46,0:15:10.70,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,when the time comes he'll have to stand guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.70,0:15:11.56,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.56,0:15:15.04,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, at 7:55 he'll get this message.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.40,0:15:19.42,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,This looks pretty suspicious...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.98,0:15:20.98,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Is this a code?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.30,0:15:22.56,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, Saiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.04,0:15:25.04,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,This part looks most suspicious:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.04,0:15:28.04,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Watermelon, pudding, squid...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.42,0:15:30.38,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,The hint is in this line...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.28,0:15:34.20,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,"Take away I and KA"...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.12,0:15:37.78,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,SU... PURIN... KURA...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.18,0:15:39.48,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Sprinkler!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.56,0:15:42.26,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,The sprinklers will be the trigger!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.28,0:15:45.18,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Akechi will deduce that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.80,0:15:48.12,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,He'll examine the school sprinklers,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.12,0:15:50.02,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,but he can't open them on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.18,0:15:52.02,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Saiko, what would you do in Akechi's position?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.10,0:15:55.22,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I would guard the sprinkler switch.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.56,0:15:57.48,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,The switch is near the staff room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.62,0:15:59.74,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Akechi guards the switch,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.74,0:16:02.14,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,and watches the sprinklers through the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.50,0:16:04.72,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,But if he guards both, PCP will...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.84,0:16:06.80,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Saiko, read it one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.80,0:16:10.28,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,This time put everything in hiragana.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.28,0:16:13.20,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Remove I and KA from the whole\Nthing and read the end of each line.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.46,0:16:15.66,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,SU...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.80,0:16:16.84,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,NA...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.84,0:16:17.80,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,BA...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.80,0:16:18.44,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,DE...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.70,0:16:20.62,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.60,0:16:22.50,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.50,0:16:24.10,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.26,0:16:26.56,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,"Launch from the sand pit,"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.96,0:16:29.22,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,"That's how I will win".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.52,0:16:31.22,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,This is really nicely done.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.36,0:16:33.16,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't see the sand pit message!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.30,0:16:33.94,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.16,0:16:38.68,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Makoto sends him a message from\Nthe sand pit explaining the trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.06,0:16:40.74,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Akechi realizes that he's been tricked.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.94,0:16:43.24,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,He can't see the sand pit very well from the staff room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.24,0:16:45.02,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,And he can't make out the identity of the person who is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.20,0:16:48.04,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Makoto picks up the fireworks and lights them off!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.04,0:16:50.78,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,For this trick, he can have a lighter on his strap.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.78,0:16:52.22,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, this is interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.22,0:16:53.52,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Watermelon and pudding...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.70,0:16:56.36,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Those connect to the earlier crimes!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.58,0:16:59.30,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Akechi is defeated, and PCP is victorious!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.30,0:17:00.86,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,This series will work.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.10,0:17:03.62,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, start writing all 5 chapters now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.62,0:17:04.20,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.84,0:17:06.40,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,You did it, Shujin!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.94,0:17:07.50,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.62,0:17:10.80,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}PCP{\i0} is going to do a series?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.12,0:17:12.06,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.06,0:17:15.66,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like its going to be more than 4 chapters long.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.84,0:17:17.56,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Their future is riding on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.96,0:17:21.44,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure Takagi-kun worked really hard to write it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.64,0:17:23.80,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I know he will put everything he has into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.80,0:17:25.14,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,You're probably right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.52,0:17:26.26,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.26,0:17:28.10,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you so happy about?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.10,0:17:29.88,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,You have to watch out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.88,0:17:32.28,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't want to lose to Takagi-kun, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.74,0:17:34.08,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.32,0:17:37.50,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if Takagi Akito puts in everything he's got,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.50,0:17:39.86,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Iwase Aiko's story will beat him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.66,0:17:43.00,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,You got 6th in the results.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.00,0:17:45.94,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,The first chapter of the series dropped a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.12,0:17:47.10,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.30,0:17:48.70,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Giri{\i0} is above us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.96,0:17:52.24,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,, Honestly, next week we might drop another place.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.60,0:17:54.66,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,This is why a series is difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.94,0:17:57.52,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,The rating won't go up until the finale.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.78,0:17:59.60,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,But how will the finale do...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.24,0:18:02.88,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, have you finished writing the last chapter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.02,0:18:04.72,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm almost done.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.92,0:18:06.52,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll call you when I finish.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.52,0:18:07.40,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.38,0:18:10.64,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Are we going to be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.08,0:18:14.88,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Giri{\i0} has passed us, and {\i1}Ally of Justice{\i0} is right behind us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.04,0:18:16.58,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.58,0:18:18.24,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,This finale is awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.48,0:18:20.76,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just like we planned. It's perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.24,0:18:22.34,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.34,0:18:23.18,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.18,0:18:25.44,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,With this we can beat {\i1}+Natural!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.64,0:18:27.96,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm... you really think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.12,0:18:29.86,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Why aren't you confident?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.36,0:18:31.30,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Saiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.40,0:18:32.76,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you like Akechi's character?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.76,0:18:33.60,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.88,0:18:35.60,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.86,0:18:39.46,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Akechi is perfect as a rival. I think he's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.76,0:18:41.24,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.62,0:18:46.30,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,This is well done. It's really interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.84,0:18:48.82,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Mashiro said the same thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.82,0:18:50.30,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? What...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.44,0:18:52.30,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.70,0:18:53.86,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.28,0:18:57.82,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,When they defeat Akechi... I\Ndon't know if I like that ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.26,0:19:01.38,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you can't have PCP lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.76,0:19:05.16,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you still have time before Mashiro-kun\Nneeds to start working on the manuscript.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.36,0:19:07.14,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Think about it until then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.80,0:19:13.48,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel like I'm missing something...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.84,0:19:15.96,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Takagi-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.96,0:19:18.68,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.62,0:19:21.76,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you having a meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.88,0:19:23.64,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I just had one with Hattori-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.64,0:19:26.36,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Really? We just finished too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.36,0:19:28.52,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,It was all secret, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.78,0:19:32.70,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Right now, Takagi-kun is Akina-kun's rival.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.38,0:19:36.52,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Iwase.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.48,0:19:39.50,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Can I talk to you for a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.50,0:19:40.12,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.92,0:19:44.00,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess I'll just get in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.76,0:19:46.56,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be going!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.88,0:19:48.50,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.50,0:19:49.72,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Is here alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.30,0:19:52.36,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Here is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.20,0:19:56.44,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard about the conditions for {\i1}PCP'{\i0}s serialization.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.62,0:19:59.32,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if they're true, I won't let {\i1}+Natural{\i0} lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.78,0:20:02.06,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I could tell that from your collaboration with {\i1}Crow.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.88,0:20:05.64,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,If we can't beat you, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.10,0:20:07.64,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,But I won't give up manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.38,0:20:10.24,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I definitely won't lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.46,0:20:13.40,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,You're getting cancelled if you lose...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.64,0:20:14.82,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I know...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.82,0:20:19.54,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,If I lose, I'll walk around the office naked.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.10,0:20:22.10,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,So you can tell jokes...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.10,0:20:23.30,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not joking!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.30,0:20:25.46,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just saying that I won't lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.30,0:20:27.08,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.18,0:20:29.94,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you always like that around me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.46,0:20:34.24,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Why? Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.24,0:20:35.46,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,In middle school...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.46,0:20:38.90,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,when you and Kaya came to my house to study.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.30,0:20:41.12,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,If I had to choose between liking you\Nand hating you, I'd have said I liked you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.12,0:20:43.78,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,W-why are you bringing that up now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.18,0:20:45.96,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I still feel the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.34,0:20:47.82,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,As a person, I don't hate you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.70,0:20:53.34,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,You've become my greatest rival as a writer,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.34,0:20:55.04,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,and I'm grateful for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.56,0:20:59.04,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I think of you as a comrade at {\i1}Jack.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.96,0:21:02.62,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,So I'll say it this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.74,0:21:05.54,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's both do our best.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.18,0:21:10.76,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I definitely won't lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.12,0:21:15.84,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I also... definitely won't lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.70,0:21:18.78,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Saiko, I figured it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.88,0:21:21.20,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.40,0:21:23.04,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Akechi and PCP...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.04,0:21:24.78,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,they're rivals!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.78,0:21:25.82,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Like with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.64,0:21:29.26,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Rivals help you reach your potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.40,0:21:31.58,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Without Eiji, Iwase, and the\Nothers, it would be boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.74,0:21:33.64,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,And we never would have gotten this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.92,0:21:37.12,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,And we're fighting those rivals right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.34,0:21:40.04,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,We have to use that in our manga, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.92,0:21:48.56,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'll launch it from the sand pit".
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.94,0:21:51.08,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,What a childish code...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.26,0:21:53.22,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,But they totally fooled me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.34,0:21:55.34,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.34,0:21:59.20,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,He must have been planning this\Nsince the watermelon incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.20,0:22:00.02,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Dammit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.24,0:22:04.00,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Another message. It's him again!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.36,0:22:06.84,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,We are the three-man group PCP.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.12,0:22:09.14,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,We had fun fighting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.42,0:22:11.84,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,So we don't mind revealing ourselves to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.22,0:22:13.90,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,We're standing right behind you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.90,0:22:15.84,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Turn around if you want to know who we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.52,0:22:23.46,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.84,0:22:26.42,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll figure out your identites on my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.42,0:22:28.04,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,I swear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.56,0:22:31.50,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,But could you tell me one thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.40,0:22:34.50,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,You said you call yourselves "PCP".
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.88,0:22:36.36,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Perfect Crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.56,0:22:38.28,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,That part I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.28,0:22:39.54,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,What is the last P?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.66,0:22:41.66,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Party!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.16,0:22:44.32,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Perfect Crime Party!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.44,0:22:46.56,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Party...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.30,0:22:49.28,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.22,0:22:58.35,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,When I struggle toward my dream
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.73,0:23:02.90,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,Those are the moments I love the most
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.27,0:23:07.53,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,I can feel our bond and will to fight
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.53,0:23:12.07,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,Our views overlap and electrify us
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.41,0:23:16.70,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,Let's improve ourselves, become what we should be
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.70,0:23:21.79,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,You can see the future in our path
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.21,0:23:26.84,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,My comrades don't agree with me
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.22,0:23:34.60,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,Our pride clashes
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.60,0:23:42.90,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,I can't let it go, I'll follow my heart from now on
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.27,0:23:45.19,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,I'm prepared
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.52,0:23:49.65,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,I'll charge right in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.45,0:23:52.78,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,Unstoppable Pride
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.07,0:24:01.21,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,There's no other choice, this is what I love and this is what I'll do
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.54,0:24:06.21,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,I don't know what tomorrow will bring
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.21,0:24:09.13,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,But I know once again (just to get by),
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.13,0:24:11.84,BakumanKaraoke,karaoke,0,0,0,,We'll do our best
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.06,0:24:17.96,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll definitely keep {\i1}PCP{\i0} going!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.96,0:24:18.62,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Hattori-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.62,0:24:19.38,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.38,0:24:23.30,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Takagi-kun... the work you've\Ndone, will it be enough to win?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.30,0:24:25.30,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,Next time: Margin and Pitfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.30,0:24:26.92,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll put all our effort in!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.92,0:24:28.04,BakumanDialogue,,0,0,0,,For the thrill of our dream!
